article.headline: Florida Gulf Coast 74, North Florida 71
article.story: FORT MYERS, Fla. (AP) -- Casey Wohlleb scored 29 points as Florida Gulf Coast edged North Florida 74-71 in overtime in Atlantic Sun Conference action on Saturday night. Wohlleb hit four crucial free throws, which put the Eagles (10-20, 6-10 Atlantic Sun Conference) up 72-68 and 74-71 in OT. He also made two free throws with 21.1 seconds left in regulation to tie the game at 59-59. Tom Hammonds scored 18 for North Florida (3-25, 1-15) and Stan Januska added 12 points. Florida Gulf Coast moved to 5-0 against North Florida all-time. The Ospreys lost their 49th straight game away from home.
